This review is LONG overdue.  The Mexico Steak House is a staple in the community.  My family has been coming here since I can remember. 30, 40, maybe 100 years for all I know, literally forever.  I remember visiting with my grandparents (Gerry & Murph) when they were alive, and being greeted with warm smiles and open arms.  Since I moved out of Chicago, this is one of my top requests anytime I come back for a visit, and no one fights me on coming here.  The food always comes out fresh.  ALWAYS. The servers are very attentive, and so friendly.    I really can’t praise them enough.  What to order?  Tacos are great, and their grande tostada. I’ve never had anything I didn’t like. My absolutely favorite is their Alambre (Steak skishkabob dinner). You guys, if you’re hungry, this will not disappoint!!   Even if I’m not THAT hungry I’ll still get it, take 1/2 home heating it in the oven and it’s STILL amazing!  Seriously, this is the best hands down.  I’m so grateful for the relationships our families have developed over the years. If you love good consistent food, and want to support local businesses, THIS is the business to support!!!  Thanks Mexico Steak House for all you do!!
